Various morphological characters of Mesoserphidae have been recorded from the latest Middle Jurassic to Early Cretaceous ( Zhang & Zhang 2000 ;
Shih et al. 2011
;
Shi et al. 2013
;
Li et al. 2016
). Compared with other mesoserphids,
Juraserphus
gen. nov. has the rare combination of both 1cu-a and 2cu-a being antefurcal in the forewing, and cells rm and r closed in the hindwing.Additionally,
Juraserphus
gen. nov. is unique among Mesoserphidae in having a female metasoma with five basal terga very short and jointly occupying only half of metosoma’s length, whilst the other half is formed by terga 6 and 7 only.
